<td style=\"width:378px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Divided into zones A-D at which different zones are allocated with different durations</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"clear: both; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>China Telecom<img alt=\"\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" style=\"float:right; height:35px; width:123px\" /></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">China Telecom offers pre-paid 4G domestic data plans payable either monthly, quarterly or 4GB, 200/), half-yearly or yearly with validity lasting for different durations. For more information, click <a href=\"http://sh.189.cn/en/index_traveller.html\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>here</strong></a><strong>! </strong>Should you require assistance, you can call their 24 hours helpline at 10000.</span><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Flying Chalks&rsquo; tip:</strong> It is strongly encouraged to purchase a local SIM card as international roaming charges are very pricey. For extra tips on making calls in China, click <a href=\"https://www.travelchinaguide.com/faq/when/general.htm\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>here</strong></a><strong>!</strong> Although uncommon now, phone booths are also available for you to make calls. Some phone booths are paid using telephone cards while others operate with coins.</span></p>\r\n','<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong><span style=\"color:rgb(255, 140, 0)\">Weather:</span></strong></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Weather in Hangzhou, Zhejiang, China, is generally warm and mild, with abundant sunshine and rainfall year round. However, you can still expect to experience 4 distinct seasons. The average temperature in Hangzhou is 15 degrees.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Spring</strong><br />\r\nSpring in Hangzhou begins in late March and ends in middle June where temperatures are warmer. It is also the period where rain starts to fall, leaving a layer of fog across the lakes, hills and pavilions. June is the month that receives most rainfall in Hangzhou. This is also the season where peach blossoms appear.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Summer&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\nThe hottest season, Summer, usually extends from late June to late September. It is rainy and hot with an average temperature of 29 degree Celsius (84 degree Fahrenheit). Of these months, July is most often the hottest despite being the &ldquo;Plum Rain Season&rdquo;.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">However from late August to end September, it is the season of umbrella where typhoons, heavy rain and strong winds take place.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Autumn</strong><br />\r\nBetween October to early December, you can expect a drop in temperatures (an average of 17 degrees Celsius), clear sky and sweet scents of Osmanthus. This is also the season of Mid-Autumn Festival.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Winter</strong><br />\r\nExpect little snow and an average temperature of as low as 3 degrees Celsius (37 degree Fahrenheit) between the periods of December to middle March. Of these cold months, the coldest period usually falls in January.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">More information on Hangzhou&rsquo;s weather can be found&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"https://www.travelchinaguide.com/climate/hangzhou.htm\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>!</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\">For more information, click&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"https://www.travelchinaguide.com/essential/useful-telephone.htm\" target=\"_blank\">here</a></strong>&nbsp;or visit&nbsp;<a href=\"http://iczu.zju.edu.cn/english/redir.php?catalog_id=247\" target=\"_blank\">Zhejiang&rsquo;s Life Guide</a>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table align=\"left\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:602px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>IMPORTANT NUMBERS</strong></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:416px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>&nbsp;General nationwide emergency hotline </strong>that can be used to call for all emergencies</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:186px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">110, 119, 120</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:416px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Police (available in 12 languages)</strong></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:186px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">110</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:416px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Police (text message)</strong></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:186px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">12110</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:43px; width:416px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Paramedics / Ambulance</strong></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:43px; width:186px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">120</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:416px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Fire Hazard</strong></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:186px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">119</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:63px; width:416px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Division of Exit-Entry Administration of Hangzhou Public Security Bureau</strong></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:63px; width:186px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">8728 0185 (Chinese)</span></p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">8728 0539 (Non-Chinese)</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:28px; width:416px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>CNTA (China National Tourism Administration)</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Office Hours: 08:30-12:00; 14:30-17:00</strong></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:28px; width:186px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">010-65275315</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n','2016-04-21 14:07:03','2016-05-16 16:27:14'),(22,22,'<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"color:#FF8C00\"><strong>Transportation:</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:18.0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Ticketing Methods</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:18pt; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">The Underground (Tube), city buses, overground, rail and river buses utilises the same ticketing system <strong>&ndash; </strong><a href=\"https://tfl.gov.uk/fares-and-payments/oyster?intcmp=1683\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Oyster Cards</strong></a> (credited smartcards). The Oyster card is the simplest, cheapest and easiest way to commute and pay for journeys on buses, Tube, trams, DLR, London Overground and National Rail Services. Find out how and where to top up you Oyster <a href=\"https://tfl.gov.uk/fares-and-payments/where-to-top-up-and-buy-tickets\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>here</strong></a>!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:18pt; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Credit deduction is based on the following table:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table align=\"center\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"font-size:13.6364px; height:90px; line-height:16px; width:650px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px; width:306px\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin-left:18pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px; width:133px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Zones 1 to 2</strong></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px; width:138px\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin-left:18pt; text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Zones 1 to 6</strong></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px; width:306px\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin-left:40px\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Peak</strong></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px; width:133px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">&pound;2.90</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px; width:138px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">&pound;5.10</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px; width:306px\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin-left:40px\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Off-Peak</strong></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px; width:133px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">&pound;2.40</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px; width:138px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">&pound;3.10</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px; width:306px\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin-left:40px\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Cash fare</strong></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px; width:133px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">&pound;4.90</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px; width:138px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">&pound;6.00</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px; width:306px\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin-left:40px\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Single bus journey</strong></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px; width:133px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">&pound;1.50</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px; width:138px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">-&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px; width:306px\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin-left:40px\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Unlimited journeys in one day in zones 1 &amp;&nbsp;2</strong></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px; width:133px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">&pound;6.50</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px; width:138px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">-&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:40px; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Another form of paying for transportation is the <a href=\"https://visitorshop.tfl.gov.uk/tfl/london-travelcard/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Travelcards</strong></a> -- paper tickets purchased at the Visitor Shops without the need for photo IDs. Travelcards allow you to travel as much and as often as you like in the specific zones that you paid for. If you purchase a travel card that is valid in zones 3-6, it will be valid for Trams as well. More information on Travelcards can be found <a href=\"https://visitorshop.tfl.gov.uk/help/travelcard/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>here</strong></a>! </span></p>\r\n\r\n<table align=\"center\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"line-height:16px; width:650px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:80px\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin-left:18pt; text-align:center\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:161px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Child Day Off-Peak Travelcard</strong></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:170px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Adult 7 Day Travelcard</strong></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:166px\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin-left:1.7pt; text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Child 7 Day Travelcard</strong></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:80px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Zones 1-6</strong></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:161px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">&pound;6.00c</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:170px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">&pound;59.10</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:166px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">&pound;29.60</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:40px; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Click <a href=\"https://visitorshop.tfl.gov.uk/help/ticket-comparison/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>here</strong></a> to find out which ticketing method is more suitable for you! Click <a href=\"http://www.ukcisa.org.uk/Information--Advice/Preparation-and-Arrival/Travel-to-your-institution#layer-3852\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>here</strong></a> to find out more about the London&rsquo;s Transport System!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>1. Tube (Underground)</strong><br />\r\nAlthough the Underground does not run to every part of the city, it is one of the fastest and most convenient ways to get around London city. Having an extensive Underground system made up of 16 lines, things may get complicated. Hence, get access to London&rsquo;s Tube map <a href=\"https://tfl.gov.uk/maps/track/tube\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>here</strong></a> or find out what are the few handy must-have <a href=\"http://blogs.which.co.uk/technology/app-review/top-five-best-transport-apps/\" target=\"_blank\">smartphone apps</a> that you should own!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Flying Chalks&rsquo; recommendation</strong>: Citymapper is free and encompasses most of the possible transport modes you can take in London!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">London&rsquo;s Underground is partnered with Virgin Media to provide WiFi to commuters. For more information on this WiFi service, click <a href=\"https://tfl.gov.uk/campaign/station-wifi\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>here</strong></a>! Details about Tube&rsquo;s adult fares can be found <a href=\"http://content.tfl.gov.uk/adult-fares.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>here</strong></a>!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Tube lines run all through the night on Friday and Saturday nights, which is great news if you are intending to stay out late during the weekends. Parts of the Underground are usually closed during the weekends for maintenance work. Do check online <a href=\"https://tfl.gov.uk/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>here</strong></a> to make sure your route is available before leaving the house!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Flying Chalks&#39; tip:</strong> Always use your Oyster card when taking the tube instead of buying </span><span style=\"font-size:14px\">one-time</span><span style=\"font-size:14px\"> single trip ticket! A single off-peak trip within zone 1 would cost &pound;2.40. The same journey would cost you &pound;4.90 with one-time tickets. Students (aged 16-25) are eligible for a 30% off Underground rides when they purchase the National Railway Card and link it up with their Oyster card!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>2. Docklands Light Railway (DLR)</strong><br />\r\nThe London DLR is an extension from the Tube, serving mainly London city (Docklands business district, <a href=\"http://www.traveldk.com/destinations/europe/england/london/sights/greenwich/\" target=\"_blank\">Greenwich</a> and some areas of East London). London&rsquo;s DLR system map can be found <a href=\"https://tfl.gov.uk/maps/track/dlr\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>here</strong></a>!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>3. National Rail / Train</strong><br />\r\nIf you are one to travel often, do check on your eligibility for a <a href=\"http://www.16-25railcard.co.uk/using-your-railcard/are-you-eligible/\" target=\"_blank\">16-25 Railcard</a> and receive a 30% discount on train journeys <strong>or</strong> if you travel in a group!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Also, take note to book in advance as tickets bought on the day of departure will cost way more! However, advanced bookings will limit your travel dates hence do check properly! Details about London&rsquo;s National Rail fares can be found <a href=\"http://content.tfl.gov.uk/national-rail-adult-fares.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>here</strong></a>!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>4. TfL Rail</strong><br />\r\nDetails on TfL Rail fares can be found <a href=\"https://tfl.gov.uk/fares-and-payments/fares\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>here</strong></a>! More information on London&rsquo;s TfL Rail can be found <a href=\"https://tfl.gov.uk/modes/tfl-rail/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>here</strong></a> while London&rsquo;s TfL Rail map can be accessed <a href=\"https://tfl.gov.uk/maps/track/tfl-rail\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>here</strong></a>!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>5. Overground</strong><br />\r\nLondon&rsquo;s Overground is a group of orbital lines that covers most of the South of the Capital with six routes. The Overground network map can be accessed <a href=\"https://tfl.gov.uk/maps/track/overground\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>here</strong></a> while its timetables can be accessed <a href=\"https://tfl.gov.uk/modes/london-overground/london-overground-timetables\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>here</strong></a>! More information on London&rsquo;s Overground can be found <a href=\"https://tfl.gov.uk/modes/london-overground/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>here</strong></a>!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>6. Buses&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n<img src=\"file:///C:\\Users\\YAP\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\msohtmlclip1\\01\\clip_image001.jpg\" style=\"font-size:13px; line-height:1.6\" />This logo is displayed on all London buses. Buses are cheaper alternatives to taking the tube.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Buses in London do not operate in zones. Hence, if you are a Travelcard user, one Travelcard will get you to most places in Greater London (out of Central London). On top of that, if your Travelcard includes Zones 3 &ndash; 6, you can use them on trams!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">London&rsquo;s bus map/ routes can be found <a href=\"https://tfl.gov.uk/maps/bus\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>here</strong></a>! More information on London&rsquo;s bus services can be found <a href=\"https://tfl.gov.uk/modes/buses/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>here</strong></a>!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">If you are using Oyster for travelling within London, do note that buses operate through a one-time payment method of &pound;1.50 per journey regardless of distance. There is no need to tap out when you get off.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Flying Chalks&rsquo; tips</strong>:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"margin-left:40px\">\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Do ensure that your Oyster card has money before boarding the buses as </span><span style=\"font-size:14px\">cash</span><span style=\"font-size:14px\"> payment is not accepted!</span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Plan your journey ahead to minimise the number of bus rides you need to get to your destination</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>7. Trams</strong><br />\r\nTrams also operate on one-time payment (pay as you go) of &pound;1.50 when using the Oyster (except at Wimbledon tapping out at the ticket gantries are required). However, unlike buses, single journey tickets can be purchased from ticket machines located in tram stops at a standard price of &pound;2.60.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Tram Passes can be bought at the following rates:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table align=\"center\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"font-size:13.6364px; line-height:21.8182px; width:650px\">\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:103px\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Contactless and Oyster</strong></span></p>\r\n			</th>\r\n			<th style=\"width:86px\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Contactless&nbsp;</strong></span><br />\r\n			&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</th>\r\n			<th style=\"width:100px\">&nbsp;</th>\r\n			<th colspan=\"3\" style=\"width:295px\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Oyster</strong></span><br />\r\n			&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th style=\"width:55px\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Pay as you go&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\r\n			</th>\r\n			<th style=\"width:49px\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Daily cap</strong></span></p>\r\n			</th>\r\n			<th style=\"width:86px\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Monday to Sunday cap</strong></span></p>\r\n			</th>\r\n			<th style=\"width:100px\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>One Day Bus &amp; Tram Pass&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\r\n			</th>\r\n			<th style=\"width:90px\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>7 Day Bus &amp; Tram Pass</strong></span></p>\r\n			</th>\r\n			<th style=\"width:102px\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Monthly Bus &amp; Tram Pass</strong></span></p>\r\n			</th>\r\n			<th style=\"width:102px\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Annual Bus &amp; Tram Pass&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\r\n			</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:55px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">&pound;1.50</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:49px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">&pound;4.50</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:86px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">&pound;21.20</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:100px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">&nbsp;&pound;5.00</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:90px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">&pound;21.20</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:102px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">&pound;81.50</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:102px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">&pound;848 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">London&rsquo;s Tram network map can be found&nbsp;<a href=\"https://tfl.gov.uk/maps/track/tram\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>here</strong></a>! More information on tram fares can be found&nbsp;<a href=\"https://tfl.gov.uk/fares-and-payments/fares/bus-and-tram\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>here</strong></a>!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>8. River Buses</strong><br />\r\nLondon&rsquo;s River buses operate on eight piers along&nbsp;Thames</span><span style=\"font-size:14px\">. Travelcard users are eligible for a 1/3 discount when purchasing adult or child fare tickets while Oyster&rsquo;s pay-as-you-go users can enjoy 10% off single fares.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">More information on London&rsquo;s River services can be found&nbsp;<a href=\"https://tfl.gov.uk/modes/river/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>here</strong></a>! London&rsquo;s River services map can be found&nbsp;<a href=\"https://tfl.gov.uk/maps/river\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>here</strong></a>!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>9. Coaches (At Victoria Coach Station)</strong><br />\r\nAt Victoria Coach station, coaches are available for journeys to and from London. Ticket halls are open from 07:00 to 22:00 daily while the departure terminals operate from 05:00 to 01:00 daily. Do remember to arrive at least 20 minutes before departure times!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Click&nbsp;<a href=\"https://tfl.gov.uk/modes/coaches/coach-companies\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>here</strong></a>&nbsp;to find a coach company! Find out more about&nbsp;<a href=\"https://tfl.gov.uk/modes/coaches/victoria-coach-station\" target=\"_blank\">Victoria Coach Station</a>!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>10. Taxi</strong><br />\r\nTaking the Taxi is the most convenient mode of transport especially when you have a lot of baggage! In the UK, only licensed &quot;Back Cabs&quot; can pick passengers off the streets (Public Hire). Hence be cautious about taking unlicensed vehicles as you would not want to pay a fine for it!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">UK Taxi fares are really expensive, especially in London. The full list of standard taxi fares can be found <a href=\"https://tfl.gov.uk/modes/taxis-and-minicabs/taxi-fares\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>here</strong></a>! Do check out their </span><span style=\"font-size:14px\">webpage</span><span style=\"font-size:14px\"> <strong><a href=\"https://tfl.gov.uk/modes/taxis-and-minicabs/\" target=\"_blank\">here</a></strong> and take note of their safety tips!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Flying Chalks&#39; recommendation:</strong> The most popular option would be to use Uber.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>11. Private Hire / Minicabs</strong><br />\r\nThese are car services (such as Addison Lee) that must be booked by telephone unlike the &ldquo;Black Cabs&rdquo;. They are slightly cheaper than the &ldquo;Black cabs&rdquo; as fares are calculated based on the total distance travelled. However, do take note of the unlicensed minicabs! Also, it is illegal for minicabs to pick passengers up without prior bookings in London. &nbsp;If you are found travelling in one, you will also be charged with an offence!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>12. Santander Cycles</strong><br />\r\n&ldquo;Hire, Ride, Return&rdquo;. Hire bicycles for short trips from as little as &pound;2 from Santander Cycles with a credit card! On top of that, no bookings are required, returns can be made to any docking station.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Click <a href=\"https://tfl.gov.uk/modes/cycling/santander-cycles\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>here</strong></a> for more information on the Santander Cycles! Click <a href=\"https://tfl.gov.uk/modes/cycling/santander-cycles/find-a-docking-station\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>here</strong></a> to find a docking station! The payment system can be found <a href=\"https://tfl.gov.uk/modes/cycling/santander-cycles/what-you-pay\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>here</strong></a>!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Flying Chalks&#39; tip: </strong>Audio maps for London&rsquo;s transport system can be accessed <strong><a href=\"https://tfl.gov.uk/maps_/audio-maps\" target=\"_blank\">here</a></strong>!</span></p>\r\n','<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"color:#FF8C00\"><strong>Banking Services:</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Opening a bank account in London can be a pain, particularly at the start of the school term when all international students are all trying to do so.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">To set up a bank account, you will be required to provide the bank:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"margin-left:40px\">\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Passport (original and photocopy) or national photo ID card</span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Letter of Acceptance from the school (proof of student status)</span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Matriculation Card (if available)</span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Updated UK address and contact number (the most common reason for rejection)</span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">An appointment with the bank branch</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Once a bank account (savings or current account) is open, the bank will usually issue a chequebook, an ATM card with deposit / withdrawal functions and a PIN for phone or online banking.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Due to strict banking regulations, each bank has different requirements to open an account, with differing minimum balances and service charges. Do visit the <a href=\"https://www.bba.org.uk/publication/leaflets/international-students/\" target=\"_blank\">British Bankers&rsquo; Association (International Students)</a> (BBA) for more information or download the <a href=\"https://www.bba.org.uk/download-file/?f=eyJ1cmwiOiJodHRwczpcL1wvd3d3LmJiYS5vcmcudWtcL3dwLWNvbnRlbnRcL3VwbG9hZHNcLzIwMTNcLzAxXC9TVDAwMDQ2ODQ0XzNQX0JCQV9JbnRlcm5hdGlvbmFsX1N0dWRlbnRzX0FFMjYwLnBkZiIsInVzZXIiOmZhbHNlfQ==\" target=\"_blank\">BBA International Students guide</a> to choosing the right bank for you!</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Flying Chalks&rsquo; tips:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:40px; text-align:justify\">1) City University will provide you with details to setting up an account with Barclays Bank during your induction!</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:40px; text-align:justify\">2) Expect a 1-2 weeks&rsquo; wait as all international students will be setting up their accounts at the same time!</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:40px; text-align:justify\">3) Make sure you bring sufficient cash to tide you through the first 2-3 weeks in London. Setting up a UK bank account and transferring money can take more time than expected, so be on the safe side and bring enough cash with you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>For Singaporeans:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Alternatively, you can choose to set up your UK account in Singapore via HSBC at least 1.5 months before departure. Do note that a processing fee will be involved and this process takes at least 4 weeks hence do check with your preferred bank for more details!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"color:#FF8C00\"><strong>Major Banks in The UK:</strong></span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>1. Barclays Bank (Recommended by City University)</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong><u><img alt=\"\" src=\"/ckfinder/userfiles/images/Barclays.gif\" style=\"float:left; height:35px; width:200px\" /></u></strong></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n<strong><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Procedures:</span></strong><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:14px\">1. An Introductory Banking Facilities letter will normally be provided to students during the induction<br />\r\n​2.&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Obtain an appointment with Barclays and a document with the address of your UK residence</span></span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">You will be able to set up a Barclays Student Bank account at no cost after providing these documents to the bank!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Homepage: &nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.barclays.co.uk/Otheraccounts/Studentaccounts/InternationalStudentsAccount/P1242620130417\" target=\"_blank\">Barclays International Students Account</a><br />\r\nLocations: <a href=\"http://ask.barclays.co.uk/branchfinder/\" target=\"_blank\">Locate a Branch</a><br />\r\nCustomer Service: <a href=\"https://www.help.barclays.co.uk/contact-us.html\" target=\"_blank\">Contact Barclays Bank</a></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>2. Lloyds Banking Group</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/ckfinder/userfiles/images/Lloyds%20bank(1).png\" style=\"float:left; font-size:14px; font-weight:bold; height:75px; line-height:22.4px; text-align:justify; width:129px\" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:14px\">Locations: <a href=\"https://www.lloydsbank.com/branch-locator/search.asp?WT.ac=Header/Navigation/Findabranch\" target=\"_blank\">Locate a Branch</a><br />\r\nInternational Students <a href=\"http://www.lloydsbank.com/assets/media/pdfs/help_and_guidance/ask_the_experts/Managing_Loans_And_Debt.pdf?srnum=2\" target=\"_blank\">Guide</a><br />\r\nCustomer Service: <a href=\"https://www.lloydsbank.com/contact-us.asp?WT.ac=Header/Navigation/ContactUs\" target=\"_blank\">Contact Lloyds Bank</a></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>3. HSBC</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/ckfinder/userfiles/images/HSBC.png\" style=\"float:left; font-size:14px; font-weight:bold; height:30px; line-height:22.4px; text-align:justify; width:160px\" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:14px\">Homepage: <a href=\"http://www.hsbc.co.uk/1/2/current-accounts/student-bank-account?HBEU_dyn_lnk=EveryDayBanking_StudentsGraduates_StudentAccount_StudentBankAccount\">HSBC Student Banking</a> and <a href=\"http://www.hsbc.co.uk/1/2/current-accounts/basic-bank-account\">Basic Bank Account</a><br />\r\nLocations: <a href=\"http://www.hsbc.co.uk/1/2/contact-and-support/branch-locator\">Locate a Branch</a><br />\r\nCustomer Service: <a href=\"http://www.hsbc.co.uk/1/2/contact-and-support\">Contact HSBC</a></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>4. NatWest</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/ckfinder/userfiles/images/NatWest.png\" style=\"float:left; font-size:14px; font-weight:bold; height:35px; line-height:22.4px; text-align:justify; width:150px\" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:14px\">Homepage: <a href=\"http://personal.natwest.com/personal/current-accounts/compare-current-accounts/student-account/student-account-international-students.html\">Banking for International students</a><br />\r\nLocations: <a href=\"http://locator.natwest.com/\">Locate a Branch</a><br />\r\nCustomer Service: <a href=\"https://supportcentre.natwest.com/app/answers/detail/a_id/4448\">Contact NatWest</a></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>5. The Royal Bank of Scotland</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/ckfinder/userfiles/images/RBS%20bank.png\" style=\"float:left; font-size:14px; font-weight:bold; height:40px; line-height:22.4px; text-align:justify; width:140px\" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:14px\">Homepage: <a href=\"http://personal.rbs.co.uk/personal/current-accounts/compare-current-accounts/student-account/student-account-international-students.html\">Banking for International students</a><br />\r\nLocations: <a href=\"http://locator-rbs.co.uk/\" target=\"_blank\">Locate a Branch</a><br />\r\nCustomer Service: <a href=\"http://personal.rbs.co.uk/personal/support-centre.html\" target=\"_blank\">Contact RBS</a></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Flying Chalks&#39; Tip:</strong> All major banks in the UK share the same ATM machines (also known here as cash points). You will not be charged any extra fees for using your HSBC card to withdraw money from a Halifax ATM.&nbsp;​</span></p>\r\n','<p><span style=\"color:#FF8C00\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Post office Services:</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>London&rsquo;s <a href=\"http://www.postoffice.co.uk/\" target=\"_blank\">Post Office webpage</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here is a list of post offices located within City University&rsquo;s postal (in ascending distances):</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Mount Pleasant (Rosebery Avenue, EC1R 4SQ)</li>\r\n	<li>Farringdon Road (39-41 Farringdon Road, EC1M 3JB)</li>\r\n	<li>Old Street (205) (205 Old Street, EC1V 9QN)</li>\r\n	<li>Murray Grove (96-97 Murray Grove, N1 7QP)</li>\r\n	<li>Grays Inn (19/20 High Holborn, WC1V 6BS)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\">It is important to pay the correct postage amount otherwise the Royal Mail will either delay delivery to the recipient or retain the letter or package. You can also return your online shopping purchases for free at the post office!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Costs for International postage can be found <a href=\"http://www.postoffice.co.uk/mail/international-standard\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>here</strong></a>!</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>City University&rsquo;s Address:</strong><br />\r\nNorthampton Square<br />\r\nLondon EC1V 0HB<br />\r\nUnited Kingdom</p>\r\n','<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"color:#FF8C00\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Medical services:</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:13.6364px\">Be glad to know that a General Clinic can be found in City University!&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Primary Care Clinic</strong><br />\r\nThe Primary Care Clinic provides NHS treatments* and private eye examinations to publics as well as students and staffs of City University. This clinic generally offers check-ups relating to the eye. More information <a href=\"http://www.city.ac.uk/health/facilities/city-sight/general-clinic\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>here</strong></a>!</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><a href=\"http://www.city.ac.uk/current-students/health-wellbeing-sport/student-health-service\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Health Service</strong></a><br />\r\nA Nurse Advisor is available for minor sicknesses, accidents and general advice. It can be found in the Student Centre Level 1, Drysdale Building, City University main Campus. They can be contacted at <a href=\"mailto:healthservice@city.ac.uk\">healthservice@city.ac.uk</a> or +44 (0)20 7040 5999.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Their opening hours are as follow:</p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"height:300px; line-height:16px; width:312px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Day</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Opening hours</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Monday</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\">9:00 - 17:00</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Tuesday</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\">9:00 - 17:00</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Wednesday</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\">9:00 - 17:00</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Thursday</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\">10:00 - 17:00</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Friday</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\">9:00 - 17:00</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Saturday</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\">CLOSED</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Sunday</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\">CLOSED</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\nCity University also encourages their students to <a href=\"http://www.city.ac.uk/current-students/health-wellbeing-sport/student-health-service/register-with-a-doctor\" target=\"_blank\">register with a GP</a>.&nbsp; GP consultations in the UK are free for all registered patients.&nbsp;City Univeristy&nbsp;is linked with some GP practices:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:40px; text-align:justify\"><strong>1. The Clerkenwell Medical Practice</strong><br />\r\nAddress: Finsbury Health Centre, 17 Pine Street, London, EC1R 0JH (Walking distance from City)<br />\r\nContact: T: 020 7833 5907, 020 7833 5906<br />\r\nClerkenwell Medical Practice will register City students living in the EC1 postcode. If not, you can also <a href=\"http://www.clerkenwellmedicalpractice.org.uk/new-patients/\">register online</a>!</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:40px; text-align:justify\"><strong>2.&nbsp;</strong><strong>The Amwell Street Practice</strong><br />\r\nAddress: 27-29 Amwell Street, London, EC1R 1UN<br />\r\nContact: 020 7837 2020</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:40px; text-align:justify\"><strong>3. Olborn Medical Centre</strong><br />\r\nAddress: 64-66 Lamb&#39;s Conduit Street, London, WC1N 3NA<br />\r\nContact: 020 3077 0044</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Search for your nearest GP on the NHS </strong><a href=\"http://www.nhs.uk/Service-Search/GP/LocationSearch/4\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>website</strong></a><strong>!</strong> Most clinics do not welcome walk-in patients so give them a call to schedule an appointment beforehand. Additionally, GPs in the UK do not dispense drugs. You will need to buy and pay for your prescription medicine at a pharmacy (such as Boots and Superdrug). In the event of an emergency, call 999 for ambulance services.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"color:#FF8C00\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Medicine</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Over-the-counter drugs can be bought at pharmacies such as <a href=\"http://www.boots.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Boots</a>! You can locate the nearest store <a href=\"http://www.boots.com/webapp/wcs/stores/servlet/StoreLocator?storeId=10052&amp;catalogId=11051&amp;langId=-1&amp;errorViewName=StoreLookupView&amp;requiredAction=locateNearestStores&amp;displayView=StoreLookupResultsView&amp;startIndex=0&amp;currentPage=0&amp;siteFlag=false&amp;postcode=EC1V+0HB&amp;town=&amp;submitLookupStore.x=107&amp;submitLookupStore.y=15\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>here</strong></a>!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The nearest Boots to City University London can be found at 25-27 Farringdon Road, while the nearest pharmacy to CASS Business School is Portmans Pharmacy located at Cherry Tree Walk, Whitecross St.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Should you require specific prescribed drugs, bring along your doctor&rsquo;s prescriptions (name and brand of drug). Do ask for a receipt for any future insurance claim!<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>*NHS treatment</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"margin-left:40px\">\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">ONLY UK nationals are eligible for NHS. However, if your full-time course of study in England, Wales or Northern Ireland is for 6 months or more, OR if you are studying in Scotland (duration does not matter), you will automatically be eligible for free NHS hospital treatment like residents of the UK!</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">11-month short-term student* route: If you were not asked to pay the immigration health surcharge when your entry clearance application was made, you will not have to pay hospital fees (Free hospital treatments). Do note however, that the waiver of the &ldquo;immigration health surcharge&rdquo; is only temporary. It will be implemented again, in future.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">&quot;Overseas Visitor&quot; route: If you are an &lsquo;overseas visitor&rsquo; do make sure that you have medical insurance coverage as you will be charged 150% of the usual tariff!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:40px; text-align:justify\">Click <a href=\"http://www.ukcisa.org.uk/Information--Advice/Visas-and-Immigration/Short-term-student-visa#RL\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>here</strong></a> for more information!</p>\r\n','<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"color:#FF8C00\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Telecommunications:</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">There are 16 mobile network providers in the UK. Most students in the UK subscribe pay-as-you-use monthly service. This option is cheap and provides them with the greatest flexibility to suspend their line anytime. To decide on which company to go with, it is best to check which network offers the best signal in your area. This <a href=\"http://maps.ofcom.org.uk/check-coverage\" target=\"_blank\">website</a> shows the network coverage.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">For those interested in signing on a contract, some telecommunications companies require a credit check before being able to open an account with them. They would expect you to have a credit history (ie. live in the UK for at least 6-months) and would require documents such as a UK bank account and proof of address in the UK. This option is not recommended for students who have newly arrived.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Listed here are some of the biggest providers for UK mobile:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>1. Vodafone</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://buddy.upce.cz/sites/default/files/partners/images/vodafone.jpg\" style=\"float:left; font-size:14px; font-weight:bold; height:50px; line-height:22.4px; margin-left:7px; margin-right:7px; text-align:justify; width:140px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Vodafone UK offers &ldquo;<a href=\"https://freesim.vodafone.co.uk/\" target=\"_blank\">Vodafone Free SIM</a>&rdquo; with &ldquo;Big Value Bundles&rdquo; that allows you to top-up (and earn reward points) and cancel at any time! (Similar to a &ldquo;pre-paid&rdquo; SIM)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table align=\"center\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"height:200px; width:700px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px; width:113px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px; width:85px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Free</strong></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px; width:95px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>&pound;10</strong></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px; width:85px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>&pound;15</strong></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px; width:95px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>&pound;20</strong></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px; width:82px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-