\r\n			<td style=\"width:239px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">&nbsp;Coobuck Coffee Shop</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:258px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">&nbsp;In front of Academic Information Center &nbsp;&amp; Library</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:239px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">&nbsp;Olympic Gymnasium snack shop</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:258px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">&nbsp;2F</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:239px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">&nbsp;Residence Hall 1 snack shop</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:258px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">&nbsp;1F</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:239px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">&nbsp;Residence Hall 2 snack shop</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:258px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">&nbsp;1F</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:239px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">&nbsp;Convenience Stores at the &nbsp;Advanced Materials&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;Chemical &nbsp;Engineering Building</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:258px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">&nbsp;B1F</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:239px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">&nbsp;Coobuck Coffee specialty store</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:258px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">&nbsp;Next to College of Law</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Flying Chalks&rsquo; recommendation</strong>:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">\r\n	<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Located on the 4<sup>th</sup> floor of Hanyang Plaza in Seoul Campus, the canteen is known to offer the cheapest meal on campus! A typical Korea meal <em>Baek-ban</em> will cost you approximately KRW 1,500 &ndash; KRW 2,000. Other dishes like Pork culet, <em>Bibimbap</em> will cost you around KRW 3,000.</span><br />\r\n	<span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Hanyang Plaza&rsquo;s peak hours are around 11:30am to 1:30pm in lunch and 5:30pm to 6:30pm in supper. Click <strong><a href=\"http://www.hanyang.ac.kr/goLink.jsp?url=http://www.hanyang.ac.kr/user/WeeklyUserList.action?reporterSeq=243&amp;command=reporter_weekly&amp;page=2&amp;parent=%2Fuser%2FindexSub.action%3FcodyMenuSeq%3D1814%26linkUrl%3D08_01_21.html%26mainFrame%3Dright%26menuFrame%3Dleft%26menuType%3DT%26siteId%3Dhanyangkr2%26sortChar%3DAAAA%26uId%3D7%26dum%3Ddum%26command%3Dreporter_weekly%26year%3D2016%26page%3D2%26reporterSeq%3D243\">here</a></strong> to find out more!</span></span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">\r\n	<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Located on the 2<sup>nd</sup> floor of the Community Center in ERICA Campus is Lunch Cok. This is also another canteen that boast its low prices in the campus. Meal prices starts at about KRW 3,000. Its operating hours are 11:30am to 2:00pm and 5:30pm to 8:50pm.&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size:14px\">Click <strong><a href=\"http://www.hanyang.ac.kr/goLink.jsp?url=http://www.hanyang.ac.kr/user/WeeklyUserList.action?reporterSeq=243&amp;command=reporter_weekly&amp;page=2&amp;parent=%2Fuser%2FindexSub.action%3FcodyMenuSeq%3D1814%26linkUrl%3D08_01_21.html%26mainFrame%3Dright%26menuFrame%3Dleft%26menuType%3DT%26siteId%3Dhanyangkr2%26sortChar%3DAAAA%26uId%3D7%26dum%3Ddum%26command%3Dreporter_weekly%26year%3D2016%26page%3D2%26reporterSeq%3D243\">here</a></strong> to find out more!</span></span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"color:#FF8C00\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Campus transportation:</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">There is no transportation available within the campus. You will have to climb the hill yourself so make sure to train well before your exchange!</span></p>\r\n','<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\">You can expect to see CCA booths, flea markets and random welfare pack distributions on Hanyang University&rsquo;s vibrant campus!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"color:#FF8C00\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Orientation program:</strong></span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">You will be welcomed by Hanyang University through a mandatory one or two-day orientation program. Apart from the usual curriculum-related briefings, you can also expect games and performances to make the entire session a really entertaining one!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">During the orientation programme, you will have to prove that you have purchased health coverage by submitting the Health Insurance Certificate (if you have not done so before arrival). Otherwise, you will be made to purchase one during the orientation which will cost you about KRW 140,000 for 6 months or KRW 200,000 for 12 months.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Health Check: Students who are not able to prove that they are tested negative for Tuberculosis (TB) will have to be tested within 30 days of arrival at South Korea; it will not be chargeable. You will be briefed on this during the orientation as well. More information <strong><a href=\"https://www.hanyang.ac.kr/user/indexFrame.action?framePath=div3_1.jsp&amp;siteId=hanyangeng&amp;leftPage=&amp;rightPage=05_02_13.html&amp;codyMenuSeq=2206#Forms and documents\">here</a>!</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"color:#FF8C00\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Buddy program:</strong></span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Hanyang University has its own buddy program where you will be paired with a local Hanyang student that can help you better integrate into life in Korea!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"color:#FF8C00\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Student clubs:</strong></span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Hanyang University houses more than 100 clubs and activities combined on its Seoul and ERICA Campus.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Club invitation events are normally held for freshmen to register and participate. During this event, some clubs such as the Band clubs, Dance Clubs, Drama Clubs and Choir clubs will put up performances for the school.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Student Council (Division of International Studies, DIS)</strong><br />\r\nThe DIS Students Council is an organization for DIS students, led and run by DIS students! Multiple events are organized by the student council to help DIS students ease into the new environment, university life as well as provide aid in enhancing their experiences. Some of the events include membership training, DIS day and the graduation ceremony.<br />\r\nVisit their website <strong><a href=\"http://dis.hanyang.ac.kr/student-union/\">here</a>!</strong> The <strong>DIS Soccer Club (FC DIS)</strong> is also a soccer club for the DIS students itself.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>The Central Clubs</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"margin-left:40px\">\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Seoul Campus has 79 Central Clubs that is made up of religious clubs, physical activities, Liberal Arts, Literature, Social Science, Exhibition, Religion and Academics.</span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">ERICA Campus has a total of 55 clubs covering 7 fields namely Public Service, Religion, Academics, Liberal Arts, Arts, Physical Activity and Ball-Game Activity!</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>College Clubs and Small Groups</strong><br />\r\nThere are approximately 80 college clubs in Hanyang University in total. These clubs bring students with common interests and thoughts together sharing close relationships with one another.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">&ldquo;Small Groups&rdquo; are targeted to students of individual college divisions encouraging deeper and more serious conversations than in college clubs.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Colorful Clubs at HYU</strong><br />\r\nAdventurous clubs such as The Montaineering Club, The Yatch Club, the Young Hanyang, The Table, Sarang-Handae and Rooters make up this group.&nbsp;Young Hanyang is one of the more popular clubs as it searches for and features parties and events for the students to partake in.&nbsp;Click<strong> <a href=\"http://www.hanyang.ac.kr/goLink.jsp?url=http://www.hanyang.ac.kr/controller/weeklyView.jsp?file=/top_news/2010/033/english1.html\">here</a></strong> to find out more about the club invitation events, Central Clubs, College Clubs and Colorful Clubs!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"color:#FF8C00\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>University events:</strong></span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">As a University that thrives for a holistic education, Hanyang University provides its students with a vibrant campus! Several event are being hosted through the year. Two of the main events are held in May and October, in both Seoul Campus and ERICA campus:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"margin-left:40px\">\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Haeng-dang-je and Ae-han-je of Seoul Campus and</span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Byul-mang-je and Milmool Festival of ERICA Campus.</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Both the Haeng-dang-je and Byul-mang-je festivals are hosted by the General Student Association to commemorate the founding of Hanyang University. These events are university-wide, last for 3 days, and begins around 15 May.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Besides the festival in May, Hanyang University also holds University-wide sports events in October. This is when intramural competitions are organized by the General Student Association.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">For more information on the annual events click <strong><a href=\"http://www.hanyang.ac.kr/user/indexSub.action?codyMenuSeq=1283&amp;siteId=hanyangeng&amp;menuType=T&amp;uId=6&amp;sortChar=F&amp;linkUrl=06_05.html&amp;mainFrame=right\">here</a>!</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Keep yourself updated with the University&rsquo;s events by following their <strong><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/HanyangUniv/\">Facebook page</a>!</strong></span></p>\r\n','<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Since Hanyang University is located near Wangsimni station (a transfer station for 4 subway lines &amp; a 10 minutes&rsquo; walk from Hanyang), you can expect to find shops and food places easily accessible!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"color:#FF8C00\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>For food:</strong></span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Although the neighbourhood where Hanyang is located in can be rather quiet, cafes and good food places can still be found in the vicinity. There is also a McDonalds is located right opposite Hanyang!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Flying Chalks&rsquo; recommendation</strong>:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"margin-left:40px\">\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Chicken Bus</span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">BBQ Buffet (Cheap!)</span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Army stew</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"color:#FF8C00\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>For daily necessities and groceries:</strong></span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">There is a big supermarket called the &ldquo;E-Mart&rdquo; located inside a large shopping complex built over Wangsimni station where you can get everything from groceries and pastries to electronics. There are also dozens of convenience stores strewn around the area.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"color:#FF8C00\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>For nightlife and entertainment:</strong></span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">There are a select few No-Rae-Bangs (Korean-style singing rooms), bars, pubs, and PC Gaming shops in the area.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Flying Chalks&rsquo; recommendations</strong>:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"margin-left:40px\">\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">If parties and nightlife aren&rsquo;t your thing, Hanyang University is located 1 station away, or 15-20 minutes&rsquo; walk, to the Seoul Forest (on Seoul Forest station), one of the recommended tourist attraction that is made up of 5 different parks perfect for a morning/ evening exercise.</span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Hongdae is a place famed for its nightlife and entertainment. It mainly caters to the younger, hipster crowd.</span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Gangnam is another place famed for its nightlife and entertainment, which also received global recognition when Korean artiste Psy&rsquo;s MV &ldquo;Gangnam Style&rdquo; went viral. As compared to Hongdae, it mainly caters to the working and more sophisticated crowd.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"color:#FF8C00\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>For shopping:</strong></span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Although the area around Hanyang University can be quiet at times, many shopping areas can be easily accessible through Korea&rsquo;s subway.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Flying Chalks&rsquo; recommendation</strong>:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"margin-left:40px\">\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">&ldquo;Express Bus Terminal&rdquo; is a highly popular place amongst locals and foreigners alike for shopping. The underground shopping features hundreds of shops with products at affordable prices. Having said that, you can always bargain for better prices!</span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Dongdaemun is another highly popular shopping haven where you can literally shop till dawn! For serious shoppers, it is near impossible to finish the entire shopping area even in one full day :O</span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Hongdae is not only known to be a great place for nightlife and entertainment. It is also an area that is known for shopping catered to the locals and foreign youths alike!</span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Aside from the above listed areas, Myeongdong and Ewha University area (for clothes are shoes) are also two of the few where you can shop till you drop!</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','<h2 style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"color:#FF8C00\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Getting from Incheon airport to Hanyang University:</strong></span></span></h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Hanyang Pick-up service</strong><br />\r\nHanyang University offers its students an airport pick-up service. Students will receive an email regarding this programme after which registration will be required. Students will also be required to pay a service fee of between KRW35,000 - KRW60,000.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">If you happen to lose your way or have difficulties finding your way, Hanyang University&rsquo;s Office of International Cooperation can be reached at +82-2-2220-0045.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Bus (the most convenient mode of transportation)</strong><br />\r\nUpon arrival at Incheon airport, bus tickets can be purchased at ticket booths located on the 1st floor, near exits 4 and 11 (outdoors), after exiting the arrival hall.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Purchase a bus ticket towards Wangsimni station (Route 6010).<br />\r\nIt will cost you about KRW 15,000.<br />\r\nBus stop: 6A or 12B<br />\r\nAlight at the last stop, Wangsimni Station.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table align=\"left\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>First bus</strong><br />\r\n			(from Wangsimni station)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Departs at 0630AM</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Bus intervals</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>30 minutes</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Last bus</strong><br />\r\n			(from Wangsimni station)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Departs at 1055PM</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:14px\">From here, you can either take the</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Train-subway from Wangsimni station (Line 2) and alight at Hanyang University (Line 2), Exit #2. This will cost you about KRW 1,250 (Transit Card) / KRW 1,350 (Ticket Fare) for a 2 minute train ride.&nbsp;</span><strong><span style=\"font-size:14px\">OR</span></strong></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Take a taxi to your final destination.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Bus services that are available at Hanyang University are 263, 302, 410, 2012, 2013, 2014, 2220, 2222 and 2411. The locations of the bus stations near Hanyang University can be found&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"http://dis.hanyang.ac.kr/find-us/\">here</a>!</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Train-Subway (All-stop train, cheapest alternative to bus)</strong><br />\r\nFrom Incheon Airport, take the all-stop train on Airport Railroad, towards Seoul Station.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Alight at Hongik University Station and transfer to&nbsp;<strong>Line 2</strong>, towards Seongsu Station.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Hanyang University is located at Hanyang University Station (Exit #2, right at its doorstep).</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">The journey will take about 1.5 hours and cost about KRW 4,350 (ticket fare) or KRW 4,250 (with transit card).</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Service Hours (as of April, 2015)</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"line-height:20.8px\">\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th rowspan=\"2\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</th>\r\n			<th colspan=\"2\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Express Train</strong></span></p>\r\n			</th>\r\n			<th colspan=\"2\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>All Stop Train</strong></span></p>\r\n			</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th>\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Incheon Airport&nbsp;</strong><strong>&rarr;</strong><strong>&nbsp;Seoul Station</strong></span></p>\r\n			</th>\r\n			<th>\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Seoul Station&nbsp;</strong><strong>&rarr;</strong><strong>&nbsp;Incheon Airport</strong></span></p>\r\n			</th>\r\n			<th>\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Incheon Airport&nbsp;</strong><strong>&rarr;</strong><strong>Seoul Station</strong></span></p>\r\n			</th>\r\n			<th>\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Seoul Station&nbsp;</strong><strong>&rarr;</strong><strong>&nbsp;Incheon Airport</strong></span></p>\r\n			</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">First train</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">05:20</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">06:00</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">05:23</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">05:20</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Last train</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">21:40</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">22:10</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">23:42<br />\r\n			23:57<br />\r\n			(final destination Digital Media City Station)</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">23:38<br />\r\n			23:49 / 24:00&nbsp;<br />\r\n			(final destination Geomam Station)</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"3\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">* Trains operate in 25-40 min intervals</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">* Trains operate in approx. 10 min intervals</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Flying Chalks Tip:</strong>&nbsp;There are many free mobile applications that you can download to help navigate Seoul&rsquo;s subway system.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">For Android users, you can download &ldquo;Subway Korea&rdquo; or &ldquo;Korea, Seoul Metro Navi&rdquo;.<br />\r\nFor IOS users, you can download &ldquo;Subway Korea&rdquo; or &ldquo;Seoul City Metro Lite&rdquo;.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Taxi</strong><br />\r\nYou can also take a taxi from Incheon airport to Hanyang University. You will receive an email with information regarding the University that contains its address.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">It will cost you about KRW 70,000 for regular taxi and KRW 100,000 for deluxe. The journey will take about 75 minutes (1 hour and 15 minutes).</span></p>\r\n','e042808fc0d2c4234741aa8ef578701754eccbfd.png','9d5115ca6c66f8e334f57271d645195f38d3039e.png','<h1><strong><span style=\"color:#FF8C00\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Expenses:</span></span></strong></h1>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Consolidated expenses of 59 returned students (in Singapore Dollars):</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:297px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:20px; width:119px\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Accommodation</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:20px; width:83px\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\">$1,582</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:20px\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Living Expenses</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:20px\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\">$4,327</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:20px\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Airfare (to-and-fro SG)</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:20px\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\">$853</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n	